main event: A military radar detected an unidentified object moving rapidly in the sky near West Hollywood, Florida in 1961.
interesting points: The object was located 30 degrees southeast of the observer's location and was moving from north to south-southeast.
The object was observed for approximately 10 minutes by a Florida Highway Patrol Captain.
The object was moving very rapidly.
The Air Force investigated the sighting and concluded that the object was likely a weather balloon.
The Air Force reported the results of the investigation in a message to the Air Technical Intelligence Center.
